27/12/2009
CARACAS, Venezuela -- Nine sailors, including three Greek nationals, who were aboard a Greek-owned ship that caught fire in the Caribbean off Venezuela's coast Friday (December 25th) have died, Venezuelan authorities announced. The other six victims were from the Philippines. Four crewmen were injured. The vessel, the "Aegean Wind", was transporting iron ore from Brazil to Houston, Texas. According to its owner, a blaze broke out in an engine room before dawn Friday, spreading upward through the vessel. On Saturday, Greek authorities announced they will investigate the incident, in co-operation with Venezuelan authorities. (Net TV - 26/12/09; ABN, AP, Reuters, AFP - 25/12/09)
